scr_943273d1f355,Customer Service is Important for Customer Retention and Loyalty,"As a business, you may think that once your product or service has sold that you are done, however, customer service after sale is the most important part to customer retention and loyalty. For example, imagine that you are an IT company who has just made a deal with a large corporation where one hundred of their employees can access your software. Your account executive has received word that many of these employees are finding the software difficult to use, and have questions about how to utilize it. You may think that your job of selling the service is over, but how you handle your customer support and service with the company will make or break how favorably they look upon your software. 

To maximize the customer retention and loyalty from your sale, you will need to have a customer support person contact them and find out how they can help ease the transition to the new software. This can be done by reaching out to the company, and asking for a list of questions about the software. Next, set up a virtual meeting with the company to answer questions and help guide them. Providing this support will make the create customer loyalty as it proves that your company cares about them after the sale. This will make it so the company will see the software favorably, and sign another contract once the deal expires.",0
